(4267, 4, '2013-11-06 11:59:52', '2013-11-06 16:59:52', 'Mohegan Indians gave Connecticut its name, which translates to "Long River Place," but the Constitution State offers much more than a 400-mile river. It''s a land of scenic coastlines, spectacular autumn views, and the home of historic events and people. This is where Mark Twain created some of fiction''s greatest characters and where Benedict Arnold committed America''s greatest act of treason. Join us on an aerial journey across a state rich in Native American legends, colonial history, and good old New England charm.', 'Connecticut', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'connecticut', '', '', '2013-11-06 11:59:52', '2013-11-06 16:59:52', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4267', 0, 'page', '', 0),
