(4271, 4, '2013-11-06 12:02:40', '2013-11-06 17:02:40', 'Georgia is where the Appalachian Mountains end and a great Civil Rights leader''s life began. A state rich in natural wonders and history, this aerial tour of the Empire State of the South captures it all. Enjoy breathtaking views of Atlanta''s skyline, Augusta''s legendary golf course, and the rugged barrier island coastline. Discover this southern state''s complex past, from the Civil War''s most notorious prison to the South''s most beloved piece of literature to the United State''s "most haunted cemetery." This is Georgia as you''ve never seen it before.', 'Georgia', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'georgia', '', '', '2013-11-06 12:02:40', '2013-11-06 17:02:40', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4271', 0, 'page', '', 0),
