(4275, 4, '2013-11-06 12:04:15', '2013-11-06 17:04:15', 'There''s more to the state of Kansas than its wide-open spaces and endless skies might indicate. It''s where great aviation pioneers took flight and civil rights heroes fought back; where Laura Ingalls Wilder documented life on the prairie; and where a fictional young girl dreamed of a life "Over the Rainbow." It''s also the home of the first battle of the Civil War and the ongoing collegiate basketball war between the Wildcats and Jayhawks. Enjoy this soaring tour through the spectacular and surprising Sunflower State. ', 'Kansas', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kansas', '', '', '2013-11-06 12:48:26', '2013-11-06 17:48:26', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4275', 0, 'page', '', 0),
