(4281, 4, '2013-11-06 14:51:35', '2013-11-06 19:51:35', 'Take a journey across distant isles, down rugged shores, and into the great wilderness seafarers once called "The Mainland." From Portland to Kennebunkport, Moosehead Lake to Casco Bay, this picturesque expedition offers a stunning bird''s-eye view of one of the most beautiful states on the Atlantic Coast. See why the Pine Tree State has attracted sailors, artists, presidents, and robber barons for centuries. Discover how Maine''s storied past, rich resources, and varied cast of characters have helped shape not just the state, but the nation.', 'Maine', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'maine', '', '', '2013-11-06 14:56:05', '2013-11-06 19:56:05', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4281', 0, 'page', '', 0),
