(4297, 4, '2013-11-06 15:19:22', '2013-11-06 20:19:22', 'Soar over the most independent-minded state in the Union: New Hampshire. Amid its stunning mountains, majestic rivers, and colonial villages exists a community of people who take their motto of "Live free or die" to heart. From an infamous poet who favored the road less traveled to the founders of both the industrial and fast food revolutions, New Hampshire is brimming with free thinkers. Witness the majesty of a state known for its passion and its politics, a state that lives up to its revolutionary cry, "Independence now and independence forever."', 'New Hampshire', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-hampshire', '', '', '2013-11-06 15:19:22', '2013-11-06 20:19:22', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4297', 0, 'page', '', 0),
