(4309, 4, '2013-11-06 15:27:34', '2013-11-06 20:27:34', 'Individualistic, eccentric, and freethinking: A unique mix that''s intrinsically "Made in Oregon." These traits belong not just to the people of this diverse and dynamic state, but also to the landscape itself. From volcanic Crater Lake to the majestic High Cascades to the perilous Pacific coastline, Oregon is a state of staggering natural beauty. From Lewis and Clark''s search for "land''s end" to the thousands of emigrants who arrived via the Oregon Trail, the state has always attracted adventurers and tenacious travellers, who keep Oregon''s spirit of adventure alive today.', 'Oregon', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oregon', '', '', '2013-11-06 15:27:34', '2013-11-06 20:27:34', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4309', 0, 'page', '', 0);
