(4313, 4, '2013-11-06 15:28:38', '2013-11-06 20:28:38', 'Join us on an aerial exploration that''s short on mileage but long on history. Known as the Ocean State, even though 60% of it is covered in woodland and parks, Rhode Island features 400 miles of pristine tidal shorelines and is the sailing capital of the world. With an incredible array of lighthouses and even more incredible stories of rumrunners, pirates, and captains of industry, this small state represents America''s progress and its excesses. To see it from the sky is to witness a tiny gleaming treasure on America''s East Coast.', 'Rhode Island', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rhode-island', '', '', '2013-11-06 15:30:36', '2013-11-06 20:30:36', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4313', 0, 'page', '', 0),
