(4315, 4, '2013-11-06 15:30:00', '2013-11-06 20:30:00', 'Explore the true spirit and rich history of the South, encapsulated in this breathtaking, first-class journey across South Carolina. It''s America''s smallest southern state, but its stories are as big as the country itself. From Fort Sumter, where the first shots of The War Between the States rang out, to Sullivan Island, the Ellis Island of Slaves, to the cypress swamp where freedom fighter Francis Marion helped turn the tide of the Revolutionary War. Take flight on a journey that showcases American history alongside pristine beaches, colorful cities, and wild spaces that equally define the Palmetto State.', 'South Carolina', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'south-carolina', '', '', '2013-11-06 15:30:00', '2013-11-06 20:30:00', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4315', 0, 'page', '', 0),
