(4319, 4, '2013-11-06 15:31:56', '2013-11-06 20:31:56', 'When Robert Frost penned "The Road Not Taken," he was writing about Vermont, and his poem perfectly captures the state''s unscathed beauty and independent spirit. This utopian state of freethinking and green living attracts all sorts of people, from artists like Norman Rockwell and the von Trapp family, to nature enthusiasts drawn to its hiking trails, ski slopes, and fiery autumn foliage. This aerial tour over the Green Mountain State captures the stunning beauty and history of a state that chose its own path, and it has made all the difference.', 'Vermont', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vermont', '', '', '2013-11-06 15:31:59', '2013-11-06 20:31:59', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4319', 0, 'page', '', 0),
