(4323, 4, '2013-11-06 15:35:37', '2013-11-06 20:35:37', 'Washington is home to some of America''s wildest spaces and also its most modern cities. Often these disparate spaces are just a few miles apart. The Evergreen State is a story of mirror opposites: A wet, mountainous, tree-covered west and a dry, flat, open east. It is home to high-tech industries and America''s oldest Native American tribes. Experience all sides of Washington State, from thousands of feet in the air, and witness its conflicting worlds merging to form a land of remarkable beauty.', 'Washington', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'washington', '', '', '2013-11-06 15:38:27', '2013-11-06 20:38:27', '', 4158, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4323', 0, 'page', '', 0),
