(4403, 4, '2013-11-07 17:05:30', '2013-11-07 22:05:30', 'Just who was the real Indiana Jones? Indy''s creators George Lucas and Steven Spielberg say the inspiration for the whip-cracking adventurer came from the explorers featured in 1930s and 40s movie serials. In turn, many writers of these serials say their inspiration came from the real-life adventures of Roy Chapman Andrews. Another source for the Indy legend is the German scholar and Grail-hunter Otto Rahn. Both embody the spirit of Indiana Jones, and lived real lives of scholarship, exploration, and danger.', 'Indiana Jones', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'indiana-jones', '', '', '2013-11-07 17:05:30', '2013-11-07 22:05:30', '', 4329, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4403', 0, 'page', '', 0),
