(4441, 4, '2013-11-08 16:13:04', '2013-11-08 21:13:04', 'With more than 7000 kilometres of spectacular shoreline, Nova Scotia is Canada’s ocean playground. From high above it becomes clear why this province is also known as one of the country''s most scenic wonders. From highlands to remote beaches, this tour slowly reveals the region''s cultural and geographic story. Travelling along the scenic Margaree River, the land rises up to a 400-million-year-old tectonic plate collision. On the scenic Bay of Fundy, the cliffs of Joggins contain one of the world’s richest fossil beds. And finally, in the hills of Cape Breton, the ancient Gaelic tongue makes a cultural resurgence centuries after it first arrived on these incredible shores. ', 'Best of Nova Scotia', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-of-nova-scotia', '', '', '2013-11-08 16:13:04', '2013-11-08 21:13:04', '', 4439, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4441', 0, 'page', '', 0),
