(4453, 4, '2013-11-08 16:23:47', '2013-11-08 21:23:47', 'The waters of the Northumberland Strait are the warmest north of Virgini, and this sheltered inlet of the Atlantic is home to some of the region’s most incredible coasts. We soar above scenic farmland, wondrous salt marshes, and the historic industrial towns along the Northumberland Strait. The 130-kilometre-long Confederation Bridge is an engineering marvel that leads to gorgeous Prince Edward Island, which has become famous for its red-mud cliffs  and miles of sandy beaches. It is incredible geographic diversity on one of the world’s favourite islands.', 'Northumberland Strait', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'northumberland-strait', '', '', '2013-11-08 16:23:47', '2013-11-08 21:23:47', '', 4439, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4453', 0, 'page', '', 0),
