(4459, 4, '2013-11-08 16:26:48', '2013-11-08 21:26:48', 'This journey to the edge of Canada ends where the waters of the St. Lawrence River empty into the Atlantic Ocean. The contours of this coast, which form the Gaspé Peninsula, are known throughout the world for their incredible remote beauty. Starting with the picturesque coastal towns of Matanie and Metis sur Mer, the landscape here slowly rises and farmland is replaced by striking mountain ranges. See the formidable cliff faces that rise high above rough waters, and the pods of blue whales that swim freely far below. ', 'Gaspé Peninsula', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'gaspe-peninsula', '', '', '2013-11-08 16:26:48', '2013-11-08 21:26:48', '', 4439, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/?page_id=4459', 0, 'page', '', 0),
