(4509, 4, '2013-11-12 14:47:14', '2013-11-12 19:47:14', 'The history of 20th-century America is on display at Doris Raymond''s vintage clothing boutique, The Way We Wore®. Decades of high fashion from iconic designers fill the racks of this boutique, each telling a story about society at the time. Enter this museum of glamorous garments and discover a treasure trove of memories associated with these pieces, as told by Doris and some of the lively characters who enter her store. If these clothes could talk, their stories would be magnificent.', 'If This Dress Could Talk', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4250-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-12 14:47:14', '2013-11-12 19:47:14', '', 4250, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/4250-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4510, 4, '2013-11-12 14:51:03', '2013-11-12 19:51:03', 'Award season means four months of high-exposure events. It also means four months of madness for the vintage clothing boutique The Way We Wore®. Follow store-owner Doris Raymond and her team as they scout vintage gems for the stylists and the stars. Will the celebs pick Doris'' fabulous pieces? The final whirlwind week leaves Doris and crew watching every step on the red carpet to see if their frocks make a splash on the Hollywood scene.', 'The Awards Season', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4254-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-12 14:51:03', '2013-11-12 19:51:03', '', 4254, 'http://staging.smithsonianchannel.ca/4254-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
